mnemonic’s Argus Threat Feed for Splunk

mnemonic’s Argus Threat Feed for Splunk is a Splunk app that enables
download and searching in mnemonic’s threat feeds. These feeds contain
domians whit known association to malicious activity.

Installation

-   Download the app from Splunkbase and install as any other Splunk
    app.

Setup

After installation, the app will ask you to configure it. The app
accepts configuration of URI, username and password for download of
threat feeds. A sample feed is preconfigured and doesn’t require a
username and password. Access to the full feed can be purchase from
mnemonic AS (mnemonic.no). Contact sales@mnemonic.no for more
information.

Features

Lookup hosts in the threat feed

Hosts, normalized to dest_dns, can be check towards the threat feed
directly from your search results using a workflow action. Any domain
can be check using the provided dashboard.

More features will follow.
